***Groan Over Marginalization DAMATURU – Preparatory to the 2023 general elections, Yobe South APC Youth Stakeholders Forum have unanimously endorsed the continuity of Governor Mai Mala Buni and appealed for more inclusion in governance through fair youth empowerment. The endorsement came after a meeting held today evening at Kaladista Luxury Hotel, Potiskum with large number of participants from the Yobe South senatorial district comprising of four local government areas of Fune, Fika, Potiskum and Nangere respectively. -Advertisement- The Chairman of the occasion, Abubakar Musa Sabo said that “as the 2023 general elections draws near, we feel it necessary to identify the APC critical youth stakeholders to brainstorm among ourselves, look inward, highlight our challenges and proffer solutions. We’re also satisfied with the unique leadership style of our amiable Governor Mai Mala Buni that is why we resolved to unanimously endorse for him”. Various speakers from the four local government areas, Musa Saidu, Auwalu Buba Kukuri, Malam Hamza, Alkali Damagum, Hamza Maidede, Ibrahim Corper, Iliya Babanyawo, Arma Ya’u Sulayman Daya and Haruna Sardauna all appreciated the incumbent administration of APC in the state for the execution of series of projects in the senatorial district but ask for more inclusion in governance and empowerment of the Youths to enable them pull out more votes for APC in the forthcoming elections. They also advised the youth group to unite, avoid politics of thuggery, shun campaign of calumny, keep away from saddism as well as come out enmass and vote for APC. They used the forum to inform the Governor Mai Mala Buni that “within his cycle some people from Yobe East and North senatorial district are sabotaging the good efforts of the Governor through marginalizing the youth of the Yobe South senatorial district. Our people are helpless and need more inclusion with better offices and schedules as it applies to the other areas”.